<subSubSection pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,414,510,536]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Biology and notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[419,668,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Valdiviomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis box="[419,668,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Valdiviomyia gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the second-largest flower fly of 
<collectingCountry box="[1044,1105,510,536]" name="Chile" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Chile</collectingCountry>
and associated with Valdivian evergreen and 
<emphasis box="[315,444,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Nothofogus</emphasis>
forests. Other data of its biology and ecology remain unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,443,582,608]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Conservation status.</emphasis>
EN under B1ab (iii) + 2ab (iii) using EOO = 
<quantity box="[948,1032,582,608]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.17" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" unit="km" value="217.0">217 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1032,1040,582,596]" fontSize="6" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">2</superScript>
, AOO = 
<quantity box="[1141,1212,582,608]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" unit="km" value="12.0">12 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1211,1219,582,596]" fontSize="6" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">2</superScript>
and three localities (or subpopulations).
</paragraph>
